dc_description_s: This data represents public land survey system (PLSS) corners for Portage County, Wisconsin in 2019. [This is a coordinate file for Public Land Survey System monuments. Many monuments are located by traditional survey methods, but a growing number are located using GPS to 3rd order Class 1 standards (1:50000). The Corner_id field is the Romportl number and can be used to hyperlink to tiesheets ex. gisinfo.co.portage.wi.us/Tiesheet_PDF/[Corner_id].pdf. Method has four values currently in use. A = GPS FGDC class, B = GPS dual observation, E = Conventional Survey, F = Map adjustment.]
uw_supplemental_s: This is an archived copy of the data held at UW-Madison. For the most recent version of this data, please visit: https://www.co.portage.wi.gov/375/Land-Information-GIS
